      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "a000b374-8696-4922-b62f-bc232695703c",
      "text": "Informal records are produced of individual transactions, and a running tally of the amount owed by one broker to another is kept. Settlements of debts between hawala brokers can take a variety of forms (such as goods, services, properties, transfers of employees, etc.), and need not take the form of direct cash transactions."
    },
